Trace the execution of the following code snippet with the array `int[][] data = {{10, 20}, {30, 40, 50}};`. What will be the final value of `sum`? Explain why the inner loop condition `data[i].length` is crucial here.
```java
int sum = 0;
for (int i = 0; i < data.length; i++) {
    for (int j = 0; j < data[i].length; j++) {
        sum += data[i][j];
    }
}
```

Analyze the following Java code snippet. Describe what it does, identify any potential issues (e.g., infinite loop, off-by-one), and explain the final value of 'result' and 'count' if 'n' is initially 10.
```java
int n = 10;
int result = 1;
int count = 0;
while (n > 1) {
    if (n % 2 == 0) {
        result *= 2;
    } else {
        result += 1;
    }
    n /= 2;
    count++;
}
```
